    "2371944": {
      "title": "Oblivious transfer is symmetric",
      "abstract": "We show that oblivious transfer of bits from A to B can be obtained from a single instance of the same primitive from B to A. Our reduction is perfect and shows that oblivious transfer is in fact a symmetric functionality. This solves an open problem posed by Crepeau and Santha in 1991."
